<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="103"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>Swiftdsl.* testlink terminated</strong><br>Swiftdsl.* (Swiftel) has officially delinked from AustNet. It's testlink was terminated tonight (10 Sept 03). We thank Swiftel and its administrator for their time and resources. <br><div class=newscredits>September 10th 7:31pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:cam@austnet.org">cam</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="92"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>Spin.* adds new staff member</strong><br>One of our Australian client servers has added its first additional staff member since linking to the network nearly a year ago. We would like to congratulate and welcome robbie as a local operator on the server. <br><div class=newscredits>June 27th 3:20pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:cam@austnet.org">cam</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="54"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>Deathstar* delinked</strong><br>New server Deathstar* has unfortunately delinked from the network shortly after permanent linking. <br><div class=newscredits>April 23rd 12:41pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:cam@austnet.org">cam</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="53"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>Two new servers for AustNet</strong><br>Kas.* vote for permlink to Austnet was concluded last night. We would like to congratulate and welcome the admin hell_ to AustNet. Vote results can be viewed <A HREF="http://users.austnet.org/public/vote.cgi?vote=110">HERE</a>. USA server Deathstar.*'s permlink vote also closed last night, resulting in a permanent position for the server on AustNet. Congratulations to chatbox the admin. Vote results may be seen <A HREF="http://users.austnet.org/public/vote.cgi?vote=111">HERE</a>. <br><div class=newscredits>April 17th 12:40pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:cam@austnet.org">Cam</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="52"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>Another network peak</strong><br>Tonight AustNet reached another milestone, with 13988 concurrent clients. Thanks to all the users who have made AustNet their online home. <br><div class=newscredits>April 7th 12:39pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:ed@austnet.org">ed</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="51"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>New Network Peak</strong><br>Last night, AustNet peaked again - reaching 13919 concurrent connections. This is about the 4th time that AustNet has reached a new peak in recent history and demonstrates that our userbase and the network are growing healthily. Congrats guys and gals! <br><div class=newscredits>April 1st 12:39pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:karl@austnet.org">Karl</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="50"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>Kas.* Testlink extended</strong><br>Routing has extended the kas.* server's testlink for an extra 30 days due to administration reasons. The server's vote and DNS entrys will be remain suspended until if/when the server is permlinked. <br><div class=newscredits>March 31st 12:38pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:cam@austnet.org">cam</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="49"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>Change of name for digital.* server</strong><br>In line with Digital's sponsors company restructuring, the server is now hosted by Infinite Networks. For this reason, the server has now changed names to infinite* and can be connected to on infinite.tx.us.austnet.org. <br><div class=newscredits>March 25th 12:38pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:hippychick@austnet.org">Hippychick</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="48"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>Deathstar.* Testlink</strong><br>AustNet continues to expand its network with another server - deathstar.or.us.austnet.org. This server is located in Portland, Oregon, USA. We welcome and wish goodluck to the administrator, chatbox. Through the testlink period, you may connect to this server via chat.anekabaru.com. <br><div class=newscredits>March 15th 12:37pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:cam@austnet.org">cam</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="47"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>New Network Peak</strong><br>Once again, on March 11th the ever growing network hit a new peak last night 13594 concurrent users! Thank you to our loyal users that choose the AustNet IRC Network to irc. <br><div class=newscredits>March 10th 12:37pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:smythe@austnet.org">smythe</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="46"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>New Network Peak (again!)</strong><br>Austnet today again reached a new peak at 13476 concurrent users. Some of the growth can be attributed to an influx of ex-Dalnet users, who have come temporarily to AustNet, found it great, and made it their permanent home. <br><div class=newscredits>March 3rd 12:36pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:hippychick@austnet.org">Hippychick</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="45"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>Dreamflow.* Permlinked</strong><br>Dreamflow has been voted upon and has been permanently linked to Austnet. The vote was passed 11 yes / 1 no / 3 abstain <A HREF="http://users.austnet.org/public/vote.cgi?vote=108" target="_blank">Vote details here</A>. Hawkon is the admin for this new server, as well as the other European server Tornado. <br><div class=newscredits>March 1st 12:36pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:hippychick@austnet.org">Hippychick</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="44"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>Kas Testlink</strong><br>Kas.vic.au.austnet.org is the latest testlinked server for Austnet. It adds another Victorian server to netspace* and yoyo*. While the server is testlinked, you can connect to it at the address /server 203.89.192.254. You can also check the application at the <A HREF="http://servers.austnet.org target="_blank">AustNet server application centre</a>. <br><div class=newscredits>February 24th 12:35pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:hippychick@austnet.org">Hippychick</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="43"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>New Network Peak</strong><br>On the 17th of February 2003 at 9:17pm AEDT, AustNet peaked to its largest <br />
user count of 13,360 connections. Thanks to all the users who help keep AustNet such a enjoyable and popular network :). <br><div class=newscredits>February 17th 12:34pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:robby@mindless.com">robby</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="42"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>Dreamflow Testlink</strong><br>Dreamflow has joined tornado.no.eu.austnet.org as the second European server connected to AustNet. While the server is still being testlinked you can show your support by connecting to irc.dreamflow.nl. Check out the server application at the <A HREF="http://servers.austnet.org" target="_blank">AustNet server application centre</a>. <br><div class=newscredits>February 1st 12:33pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:ed@austnet.org">Ed</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="41"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>New Network Peak</strong><br>On 20th January AustNet reached a new peak - with 13300 concurrent connections. Some of this growth can be attributed to gaining users from the recent DalNet misfortunes. <br><div class=newscredits>January 28th 12:32pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:karl@austnet.org">Karl</a></div></td></tr>
</table>              </p>
              </td>
